    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan I've built after thoroughly reading the codebase:\n\n## Plan: `uv cache stats` subcommand\n\n**4 files to touch, 1 new file to create:**\n\n### What I found in the codebase\n\n- `CacheBucket::iter()` yields **10 buckets** (Wheels, SourceDistributions, FlatIndex, Git, Interpreter, Simple, Archive, Builds, Environments, Binaries — `Python` is deliberately excluded from `iter()`)\n- `CacheBucket` already implements `Display` via `to_str()` → outputs names like `\"wheels-v6\"`, `\"sdists-v9\"`, etc.\n- `Cache::bucket(bucket)` → `PathBuf` pointing to each bucket subdirectory\n- `diskus::DiskUsage::new(vec![path]).count_ignoring_errors()` is the established disk-size pattern from `cache_size.rs`\n- `human_readable_bytes` is already re-exported in `commands/mod.rs`\n- **No preview flag needed** — unlike `cache_size`, the new command won't be gated behind a preview feature\n\n### Changes\n\n1. **`crates/uv-cli/src/lib.rs`** — Add `Stats(StatsArgs)` to `CacheCommand` enum + new `StatsArgs` struct (mirrors `SizeArgs` exactly)\n2. **`crates/uv/src/commands/cache_stats.rs`** *(new)* — Iterate `CacheBucket::iter()`, measure each bucket's size with `DiskUsage`, print `{bucket}: {size}` per line, then `total: {size}`. Handles missing cache root and missing individual bucket dirs gracefully.\n3. **`crates/uv/src/commands/mod.rs`** — Add `mod cache_stats;` and `pub(crate) use cache_stats::cache_stats;`\n4. **`crates/uv/src/lib.rs`** — Add dispatch arm `CacheCommand::Stats(args) => commands::cache_stats(&cache, args.human, printer)` after the `Size` arm",
